contenido.esp:
Si sus estudiantes presentan dificultades para comprender el cálculo de la UF para el día 5 de Enero, puede modelar el calculo y desafiar que realicen el del 9 de enero: <br><br>\begin{eqnarray}
UF_{día\,5}&amp;=&amp;\text{UF último día mes anterior}\cdot(factor_{dic})^5 \\
UF_{día\,5}&amp;=&amp;30\,991,74\cdot(1,000160901)^5 \\
UF_{día\,5}&amp;=&amp;31\,016,68
\end{eqnarray}

contenido.eng:
According to the regulations of the Central Bank, the UF is readjusted on a daily basis. Its value is calculated at the beginning of each month for the period between the 10th of said month and the 9th of the following, according to the variation experienced by the Consumer Price Index (CPI). <br><br>

The UF calculation process for any day of the month is detailed below. <br<<br>

<li>Formula for calculating the UF daily readjustment factor:</li><br>

\begin{eqnarray}
Factor=[1 \frac{IPC_-1}{100}]\Huge^\frac{1}{d}
\end{eqnarray}<br><br>
</br<<br>
Factor= daily readjustment factor of the UF.<br>
IPC_-1 = Percentage variation of the CPI registered immediately before.<br>
d= Number of days included in the period for which the value of the UF is calculated <br><br>
